\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Index idx
range none
pageformat default
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
child mortality
\end_layout

\end_inset

In recent decades,
 child mortality throughout the world has declined sharply.
 However,
 it still varies greatly among the world's countries.
 Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab: barnadödlighet"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 describes the average child mortality per continent in 1950 and 2016.
 Both in 1950 and 2016,
 child mortality was highest in Africa.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
However,
 child mortality has also decreased the most in the African countries,
 from approximately 300 per 1,000 children in 1950,
 to being down to 62.7 deceased children per 1,000 under 5 years of age in 2016.
 During the same period,
 child mortality in the countries in Europe decreased from 86.7 in 1950 to 4.9 in 2016.
