nolink "false"

\end_inset

.
 The points along the black line show the combined values of 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 (the horizontal axis) and 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 (the vertical axis) at the whole numbers 0 to 5.
 Two combined values of the variables 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 can be written with parentheses 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(x,y\right)$
\end_inset

,
 which represents a point in the graph.
 The point 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(x,y\right)=\left(2,20\right)$
\end_inset

 has the values 
\begin_inset Formula $x=2$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y=20$
\end_inset

.
 The point where 
\begin_inset Formula $x=y=0$
\end_inset

 can be written 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(x,y\right)=\left(0,0\right)$
\end_inset

 and is called the zero point or origin.
 
