\begin_layout Standard
The black line is leaning to the upper right corner of the graph.
 The coefficient 10 in the equation indicates how much variable 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 changes each time variable 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 increases by 1.
 When 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 increase from 1 to 2,
 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 increase from 10 to 20.
 In the graph we may see this by following the black line and comparing the values on the x- and y-axis.
