\begin_layout Standard
Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Härledning-av-pq-formeln"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 shows how the quadratic formula can be derived.
 In the left column a general example with letters is given step by step.
 In the right column we go through the same thing for the following equation,
 where we solve for 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
2x^{2}+3x+\frac{1}{4} & =0\label{eq: pq-härledning 1}
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:parentes kvadrat"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 we went through the squaring rule for parentheses:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\left(x+d\right)^{2}=x^{2}+2dx+d^{2}\label{eq: kvadreringsregel repetition}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq: pq-härledning 1"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 we start by moving 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{1}{4}$
\end_inset

 to the right side and dividing everything by 2:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
2x^{2}+3x & =-\frac{1}{4}\\
x^{2}+\frac{3}{2}x & =-\frac{1}{8}\nonumber 
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this equation the fraction 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{3}{2}$
\end_inset

 now corresponds to the term 
\begin_inset Formula $2d$
\end_inset

 in equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq: pq-härledning 1"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

.
 The expression 
\begin_inset Formula $d^{2}$
\end_inset

 is therefore 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\frac{3}{2}\right)^{2}$
\end_inset

.
 We add this to both sides and rewrite:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
x^{2}+\frac{3}{2}x+\left(\frac{3}{2}\right)^{2} & =-\frac{1}{8}+\left(\frac{3}{2}\right)^{2}\\
\left(x+\frac{3}{2}\right)^{2} & =-\frac{1}{8}+\left(\frac{3}{2}\right)^{2}\nonumber 
\end{align}

\end_inset

We take the square root of both sides and move everything except 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 to the right side:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
x^{*} & =-\frac{3}{2}\pm\sqrt{-\frac{1}{8}+\left(\frac{3}{2}\right)^{2}}
\end{align}

\end_inset

The square root of a number is given by both a negative and a positive value,
 which is symbolized by the plus-minus sign 
\begin_inset Formula $\pm$
\end_inset

.
 This gives us two solutions to equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq: pq-härledning 1"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
x_{1}^{*} & =-\frac{3}{2}+\sqrt{-\frac{1}{8}+\left(\frac{3}{2}\right)^{2}}\\
x_{2}^{*} & =-\frac{3}{2}-\sqrt{-\frac{1}{8}+\left(\frac{3}{2}\right)^{2}}\nonumber 
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

