In this case we can without difficulty also use substitution and reach the same result,
 for example by taking the definition of y in row 2 and substituting this into row 1.
 From this we can solve out 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
x^{2}-10 & =20-2x^{2}\\
x & =\pm10^{1/2}\nonumber 
