 where function 
\begin_inset Formula $f\left(x\right)=1/x$
\end_inset

 goes toward positive infinity 
\begin_inset Formula $+\infty$
\end_inset

 as 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 approaches 0 for positive numbers and toward negative infinity 
\begin_inset Formula $-\infty$
\end_inset

 for negative numbers:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
\lim_{x\rightarrow0^{+}} & f\left(x\right)=\frac{1}{x}=+\infty\\
\lim_{x\rightarrow0^{-}} & f\left(x\right)=\frac{1}{x}=-\infty\nonumber 
\end{align}

\end_inset


