For describing what constitutes an average value for a collection of values,
 we use what are called measures of central tendency.
 Two examples of measures of central tendency are mean (sum divided by number) and median (the middle value).
 We introduced both of these measures in section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
