\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "fig:Varians-för-två"

\end_inset

Variance for variables 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|a\right|$
\end_inset

 is the absolute value of the constant a.
 Now we shall calculate (estimate) the variance with four observations for two variables:
 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

.
 Variable 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 has the values 3,
 4,
 6 and 7.
 Variable y has the values 3,
 2,
 5 and 4.
 Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Variablerna x y några beräkningar k18"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 summarizes the calculations we need.
 We use the definition of variance from equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq: varians def 2, div n-1"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
var\left(x\right) & =\frac{\sum_{i}\left(x_{i}-\bar{x}\right)^{2}}{n-1}=\frac{10}{3}\label{eq: varians för x och y}\\
var\left(y\right) & =\frac{\sum_{i}\left(y_{i}-\bar{y}\right)^{2}}{n-1}=\frac{5}{3}\nonumber 
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The variance for variable 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 is larger than the variance in variable 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

.
 This indicates that the values in 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 are more spread out from the mean compared to the spread in variable 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

.
 Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Varians-för-två"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 illustrates deviations from the mean for each respective variable.
 In the heading for each respective graph,
 mean and variance are reported.
 To calculate standard deviation for variables 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

,
 we take the positive square root of the variance:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
s_{x}= & \sqrt{\frac{\sum_{i}^{n}\left(x_{i}-\bar{x}\right)^{2}}{n-1}}=+\sqrt{\frac{10}{3}}\approx10.05\label{eq: standardavvikelse ex1 x y}\\
s_{y}= & +\sqrt{\frac{5}{3}}\approx0.745\nonumber 
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

