\begin_layout Standard
The observations for the variables 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

 are described in table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Beräkningar-med- z k"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 together with the calculations we need to estimate the regression model in equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq: ols reg modell 2"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

.
 For the slope coefficient 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\beta}$
\end_inset

 we get:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
\hat{\beta} & =\frac{\sum_{i}\left(K_{i}-\bar{K}\right)\left(Z_{i}-\bar{Z}\right)}{\sum_{i}\left(K_{i}-\bar{K}\right)^{2}}=\frac{-8}{16}=-\frac{1}{2}
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For the other coefficient 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\alpha}$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
\hat{\alpha} & =\bar{Z}-\hat{\beta}\bar{K}=1,5-\left(-\frac{1}{2}\right)2=2.5
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\beta}<0$
\end_inset

 means that the regression line's slope is negative and that we have a negative covariation between the four observations for 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

.
 We now set up an equation for predicted 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{Z}$
\end_inset

:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
\hat{Z_{i}} & =\hat{\alpha}+\hat{\beta}K_{i}=2.5-\frac{1}{2}K_{i}\label{eq: beräknade ekvationen ex 2}
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With the help of this and the observed values for variable 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

,
 we estimate four values for predicted 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{Z}$
\end_inset

,
 which are described in table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Beräkning-av residual e"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

.
 With 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{Z}$
\end_inset

 we then estimate the four residuals 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{U}$
\end_inset

,
 which are described in the same table.
 The four observations and the regression line that can be drawn with equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq: beräknade ekvationen ex 2"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 are illustrated in figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig: ols ex 2"
