\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "fig: varians kolada inc life"

\end_inset

Life expectancy and GDP per capita:
 difference to the mean
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The results are illustrated in figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig: varians kolada inc life"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 with deviations from the mean,
 with life expectancy in the graph to the left and GDP per capita in the graph to the right.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Standard deviation for life expectancy 
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

 is:
\begin_inset Index idx
range none
pageformat default
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
standard deviation
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
s_{L}=\sqrt{var\left(L\right)} & =\sqrt{\frac{\sum_{i}^{n}\left(L_{i}-\bar{L}\right)^{2}}{n-1}}\approx8.26
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Standard deviation for income 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
s_{G}=\sqrt{var\left(G\right)} & =\sqrt{\frac{\sum_{i}^{n}\left(G_{i}-\bar{G}\right)^{2}}{n-1}}\approx19.336
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The results show that life expectancy has a standard deviation of 0.98 years and average income has a standard deviation of 21.5.
 We have an idea that life expectancy and income can be expected to covary linearly,
 even though we do not have a theory about a causal relationship.
 We therefore estimate the covariance between the variables.
 Large parts of the calculation are found in table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Beräkningar-för- d och m"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Index idx
range none
pageformat default
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
covariance
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Index idx
range none
pageformat default
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
covariation
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
cov\left(L,G\right) & =\left(\frac{1}{n-1}\right)\sum_{i}\left(L_{i}-\bar{L}\right)\left(G_{i}-\bar{G}\right)\approx151.696\label{eq: cov d och m}
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The result indicates a positive covariance,
 greater GDP is associated with on average higher average life expectancy.
 As was described in section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:Kovarians"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 this measure is often difficult to interpret.
 We cannot assess whether the covariation we find should be regarded as high or low (strong or weak).
\end_layout

