\begin_layout Standard
The result 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\alpha}_{2}=0.4057$
\end_inset

 means that 1,000 USD higher GDP per capita on average coincides with approximately 0.4057 years longer average life expectancy (almost five months).
 Our y-intercept 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\alpha_{1}}$
\end_inset

 equals 65.758,
 which can be interpreted as that if there had existed a country with zero GDP per capita 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(G_{i}=0\right)$
\end_inset

 the average life expectancy there would have been 65.758 years.
 Let us now estimate predicted average life expectancy 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{L_{i}}$
\end_inset

 and the residuals 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{e_{i}}$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
\hat{L_{i}} & =\hat{\alpha_{1}}+\hat{\alpha_{2}}G_{i}\\
\hat{e_{i}} & =L_{i}-\hat{L_{i}}\nonumber 
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The results are described in table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Beräkningar-för- d och m"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 and illustrated in figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig: ols livslängd inkomst - sex länder"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

.
 Please check that the table is correct.
 Next we estimate 
\begin_inset Formula $R^{2}$
\end_inset

 for the regression model in equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq: socialt ex sex länder regress1, litet urval"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Index idx
range none
pageformat default
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
coefficient of determination
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Index idx
range none
pageformat default
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
r@
\begin_inset Formula $R^{2}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
R^{2} & =1-\frac{\sum_{i}\left(L_{i}-\hat{L_{i}}\right)^{2}}{\sum_{i}\left(L_{i}-\bar{L}\right)^{2}}\approx1-\frac{33.4}{341}\approx0.902
\end{align}

\end_inset

This indicates that approximately 90% of the variation in average life expectancy in these countries could be explained by the regression model and the variation in our explanatory variable,
 GDP per capita.
\end_layout

