Statistical analysis is fundamentally a quantitative method.
 We use numbers to calculate new numbers.
 If we instead want to study other types of data,
 this needs to be quantified in some form and written with numbers.
 There are many situations where we may benefit from statistical analyses of data material that at first glance is not associated with statistics.
 Here follows a simple example as illustration.
\begin_inset Float table
placement document
alignment document
wide false
sideways true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset CommandInset label
