\begin_layout Standard
Now we will estimate a regression model based on some observations.
 For this we reuse the fictitious variables 
\begin_inset Formula $Y,X$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

 with four observations each that we used in chapter 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "chap: ols"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 when we introduced the least squares method.
 All three variables are reported in table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Variablerna y x z"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 with some calculations that we need.
 In section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec: minstakvadratmetoden ols"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 we used the variables 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 to estimate the regression model 
\begin_inset Formula $Y_{i}=a+bX_{i}+V_{i}$
\end_inset

 and found then that 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{a}=1$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{b}=0.5$
\end_inset

.
 Now we will estimate the coefficients for the following regression model:
\begin_inset Index idx
range none
pageformat default
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
regression!model
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Index idx
range none
pageformat default
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
regression!three variables
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
y_{i}=a+bx_{i}+cz_{i}+v_{i}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where Y,
 X and Z are the variables,
 a,
 b and c are the coefficients we will estimate and V is the error term.
 In equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq: OLS-konstanterna b och c"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 we have the definitions for how we estimate 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{b}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{c}$
\end_inset

.
 In table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Variablerna y x z"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 we have some of the results we need:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
\hat{b} & =\frac{\left(5\right)\left(9\right)-\left(-6\right)\left(-4\right)}{\left(10\right)\left(9\right)-\left(-4\right)^{2}}\approx0.28\\
\hat{c} & =\frac{\left(-6\right)\left(10\right)-\left(5\right)\left(-4\right)}{\left(10\right)\left(9\right)-\left(-4\right)^{2}}\approx-0.54\nonumber 
