\begin_layout Standard
The coefficient 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{b}$
\end_inset

 is negative,
 which means that the variable 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 has a negative covariation with 
\begin_inset Formula $W$
\end_inset

.
 Our dummy variable is defined 
\begin_inset Formula $G=1$
\end_inset

 for women.
 Variable 
\begin_inset Formula $W$
\end_inset

 is associated with an 2.53 units lower value for women compared to men,
 which means that women on average in 2020 had 2.53 lower earnings per hour than men in these countries.
