\begin_layout Standard
The last row contains the rounded results 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{a}=2.9$
\end_inset

,
 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{b}=0.3$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{c}=-0.5$
\end_inset

.
 This is the same thing we arrived at in section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec: ols på tre variabler"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

.
 In section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec: OLS ex 2"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 we used four observations for the variables 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

,
 which are repeated in table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Variablerna z och k k20"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

.
 With these observations we estimated the regression model 
\begin_inset Formula $Z=\alpha+\beta K+\epsilon$
\end_inset

,
 where 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon$
\end_inset

 is the error term and 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta$
\end_inset

 are the model's coefficients,
 which we found were 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\alpha}=2.5$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{\beta}=-0.5$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With matrices we write this regression model as 
\begin_inset Formula $Z=KB+E$
\end_inset

,
 where 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

 is the explained variable,
 B is a matrix with the coefficients 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta$
\end_inset

,
 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

 is a column matrix with the explanatory variable and E is the error terms.
 The estimator can in this case be written:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
\hat{B} & =\left(K^{T}K\right)^{-1}K^{T}Z
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This gives us the following estimates:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
\left[\begin{matrix}\hat{\alpha}\\
\hat{\beta}
\end{matrix}\right] & =\left(\left[\begin{matrix}1 & 1 & 1 & 1\\
0 & 0 & 4 & 4
\end{matrix}\right]\left[\begin{matrix}1 & 0\\
1 & 0\\
1 & 4\\
1 & 4
\end{matrix}\right]\right)^{-1}\left[\begin{matrix}1 & 1 & 1 & 1\\
0 & 0 & 4 & 4
\end{matrix}\right]\left[\begin{matrix}1\\
4\\
0\\
1
\end{matrix}\right]=\left[\begin{matrix}2.5\\
-0.5
\end{matrix}\right]
\end{align}

\end_inset

which is the same result as in section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec: OLS ex 2"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

