caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 describes calculated critical values for the t-distribution based on degrees of freedom,
 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

,
 and percentage probability,
 where the percentages describe significance level.
 As before,
 these are values from the cumulative distribution function 
\begin_inset Formula $F\left(x\right)$
\end_inset

,
 depending on number of degrees of freedom.
 The percentages,
 the significance level,
 refer to what proportion of the distribution is equal to or less than this t-value.
