 and look in that case at row 
\begin_inset Formula $k=10$
\end_inset

.
 We cannot see the value 2 in the table,
 but since we have 
\begin_inset Formula $x=1.81$
\end_inset

 for 95% and 
\begin_inset Formula $x=2.23$
\end_inset

 for 97.5%,
 this means that between 95 and 97.5% of the distribution is equal to or less than 
\begin_inset Formula $F\left(x=2\right)$
\end_inset

.
 This is illustrated in figure 
