\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "fig:Histogram residualer log bnp trend tid"

\end_inset

The residuals from the regression model in eq.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq: gauss-markov log bnp trend"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The bars show the number of residuals.
 In the graph we have also drawn a curve for a normal distribution with the same mean and standard deviation as the estimated residuals (our observations).
 The bars to the left in the graph indicate that many residuals have a value around 
\begin_inset Formula $-4,000,0000$
\end_inset

.
 There is a tail to the right in the graph,
 with scattered values above 5,000,000.
 Thus,
 even this simple comparison gives a relatively clear indication that the residuals do not follow the normal distribution particularly well.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let us look at another example.
 In section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec: ols kolada alla kommuner livslängd inkomst"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 we compared the covariation between life expectancy and earnings.
 Let us briefly recapitulate the regression analysis,
 by repeating the regression model:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
L_{i}=a+bM_{i}+e_{i}\label{eq: gauss markov kolada reg model}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $L_{i}$
\end_inset

 is mean life expectancy for the inhabitants in country 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

,
 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{i}$
\end_inset

 is GDP per capita,
 the letters 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 are the coefficients and 
\begin_inset Formula $e_{i}$
\end_inset

 is the error term.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig: gauss markov residualanalys Kolada inkomst och livslängd"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 illustrates estimated results from this regression model in two graphs.
 The graph to the left shows the linear covariation where the regression line is drawn based on the regression model in equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq: gauss markov kolada reg model"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

.
 In the graph to the left we see a positive covariation between life expectancy and earnings.
 This result we have compared earlier in several different examples and we will therefore not go into the coefficients 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{a}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{b}$
\end_inset

 in more detail.
 
\begin_inset Float figure
placement document
alignment document
wide false
sideways false
status open

