\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To show multiple modes,
 we select cells B1 to B4.
 Without clicking anywhere else,
 we now write =MODE.MULT(A:A).
 Press Ctrl + Shift + Enter.
 This command creates what is called an array formula.
 When MODE.MULT() is used as an array formula,
 it returns multiple modes,
 if there are multiple.
 If only one value in the collection is most common,
 the function returns the same value in all cells.
 
\end_layout

