\begin_layout Standard
Excel also has ready-made functions for statistical tests based on several commonly occurring probability distributions.
 The normal distribution is symmetric with half of the probability distribution below and above the mean respectively.
 This means that the distribution function 
\begin_inset Formula $F\left(-x\right)=1-F\left(x\right)$
\end_inset

.
 For a one-tailed statistical test with the normal distribution and confidence level 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha=0.05$
\end_inset

,
 we set the critical value in one tail so that the calculated statistic must be greater than 95% of the distribution.
 For a two-tailed test with the same 
\backslash
alpha,
 the critical value in each respective tail corresponds to 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha/2=0.025$
\end_inset

,
 which means that the critical region in each respective tail corresponds to 2.5% of the distribution.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
placement document
alignment document
wide false
sideways false
status open

