reference "fig:En-regressionsmodell-per bnp per arbetstimme excel"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 shows how this can look in an Excel sheet.
 In cells B11:E16 we use the LN() function to take the natural logarithm of the values in cells B2:E7.
 In cells G11:G16 we use the LINEST() function to estimate a regression model per row 11–16,
 which gives us an estimate per country.
\end_layout

