\family typewriter
cells()
\family default
,
 in whose parentheses we can specify which results are presented and in what format the numbers should be displayed.
 The next option is 
\family typewriter
varlabels()
\family default
 which we can use to define which labels should be used for the explanatory variables,
 which is written in the form varlabel(variable 1 label 1 variable 2 label 2).
 We use the option 
\family typewriter
mlabels()
\family default
 to set headings on the columns,
 which names the regression models we estimated.
 With the option stats() we can instruct whether we want to present some other type of result,
