\begin_layout Section
Creating plots
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sec:Skapa-diagram-i stata"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Stata has a large number of functions and options for creating different types of charts.
 If we want to create a histogram we can use the function histogram.
 This function has different options that can affect the appearance of the chart,
 which we can read more about on the function's help page.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Before we create the histogram we will create a random variable,
 whose values are drawn from a normal distribution,
 which we can do using the function 
\family typewriter
rnormal()
\family default
.
 Each observation is drawn from a known population but exactly which value each observation gets is drawn randomly,
 using the computer's random generator.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The computer's random generator is however not more random than that we can control its conditions.
 If we want to be sure that the random draw that creates the variable gives exactly the same result every time we run the script,
 we can define a random seed with the function set seed.
 We then write set seed and any number,
 for example set seed 1.
 Read more about random seeds in this function's help section.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Here follows an example where we first define the random seed to the value 1,
 create 300 observations for a variable based on a normal distribution and then create a histogram with the function histogram:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\family typewriter
clear all
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\family typewriter
* Set number for random seed
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\family typewriter
set seed 1
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\family typewriter
set obs 300
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\family typewriter
* Create variable x from the standard normal distribution
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\family typewriter
generate x = rnormal()
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\family typewriter
* Display a histogram over x
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\family typewriter
histogram x
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
placement document
alignment document
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename ../../___arkiv/Datorprogram för samhällsvetare/texten/stata mitt_histogram.png
	scale 50

\end_inset


\end_layout

