\begin_layout Standard
Index for a variable year t is calculated in the following way:
\begin_inset Index idx
range none
pageformat default
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\lang swedish
indexberäkning!R
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\text{Index}_{t}=\frac{\text{Value}_{t}}{\text{Value}_{\text{base year}}}*100\label{eq:index def-1-1}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where value refers to the value for the variable we want to create an index for.
 We will now calculate an index for GDP per capita,
 compare section 
