 477800,
 483500,
 487300,
 488800))
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To then calculate an index for GDP we can use the following command where we use the function 
\family typewriter
mutate()
\family default
 to add a variable to the table with the index calculation:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\family typewriter
bnp_data <- bnp_data %>% 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\family typewriter
arrange(year) %>% 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

