\begin_layout Section
Create plots
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There are many functions in R that can be used to create graphics and charts.
 We will here introduce a few parts of the ggplot2 package,
 which is included in the tidyverse package.
 By loading tidyverse,
 ggplot2 is also loaded.
 In the ggplot2 package we can create charts using the function ggplot().
 It works in the following way:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Specify data table with the columns that should be displayed in the chart.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Specify which columns in the table should be displayed,
 and define how the values from these columns should be illustrated in the chart.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
After 
\family typewriter
ggplot()
\family default
 we must specify one or more functions of type geom_point(),
 geom_line(),
 geom_\SpecialChar ldots
 to define what type of chart should be displayed.
 For example,
 geom_point() defines that we want to create a scatter plot.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
We can add additional ggplot2 functions after ggplot() and geom_point() with a plus sign + between (that is,
 not the pipe function %>%).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Often we use the function aes() in the parentheses for ggplot().
 "Aes" is an abbreviation for aesthetics.
 In the parentheses for aes() we specify which variable should be displayed in what way in the chart.
 Below follows code that draws a chart with ggplot() with lines and points.
 The points are created with the function geom_point().
 The lines are created with geom_line().
 These functions reuse the information we specified in the parentheses for ggplot() and aes().
 The result is shown in figure [fig:
 r graf 1].
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\family typewriter
tibble(time=2015:2022,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\family typewriter
\begin_inset Formula $\qquad$
\end_inset

 my_variable = c(3,2,4,5,3,5,6,
 4)) %>%
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\family typewriter
ggplot(aes(x=time,
 y=my_variable)) +
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\family typewriter
geom_point() +
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\family typewriter
geom_line()
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
